                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/157.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 13. Minister for Foreign. Affairs informs me that in view
                    of the objections of the Government of the United States the Duncan railway
                    contract will be withdrawn from the Assembly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
